00:21:15.720 --> 00:21:18.740
They partnered with us in a
groundbreaking series of

00:21:18.740 --> 00:21:22.470
inventive online happenings,
that I really feel was an

00:21:22.470 --> 00:21:24.950
amazing game changer
for fashion.

00:21:24.950 --> 00:21:27.130
And this was such an
exceptional, well executed

00:21:27.130 --> 00:21:29.050
campaign, I could
go on and on.

00:21:29.050 --> 00:21:31.540
But I really just want to focus
on two parts that I

00:21:31.540 --> 00:21:34.360
think you guys will
be interested in.

00:21:34.360 --> 00:21:37.770
The first was the Be The Model
component afforded a rare

00:21:37.770 --> 00:21:40.120
opportunity for fans to
get a model's eye

00:21:40.120 --> 00:21:41.450
view of Fashion Week.

00:21:41.450 --> 00:21:44.710
There were Hangouts with
the top models.

00:21:44.710 --> 00:21:49.380
And at Topshop's flagship store,
fans could enter a

00:21:49.380 --> 00:21:53.150
special Google+ booth where
they try on their favorite

00:21:53.150 --> 00:21:56.910
look and take a picture, and
it would upload it to the

00:21:56.910 --> 00:22:01.460
Google+ Event Page, which really
bridged that online and

00:22:01.460 --> 00:22:03.350
offline gap.

00:22:03.350 --> 00:22:07.280
And Be the Buyer component saw
the launch of a Hangout app

00:22:07.280 --> 00:22:10.150
where for the first time in
fashion history, users could

00:22:10.150 --> 00:22:12.370
pick and choose their favorite
items and share them with

00:22:12.370 --> 00:22:14.640
their friends in a Hangout.

00:22:14.640 --> 00:22:22.950
So Topshop rewarded its best
collection of outfits with a

00:22:22.950 --> 00:22:26.300
Fabulously Free Shopping
Spree as well.

00:22:26.300 --> 00:22:30.990
And they promoted this Hangout
app exhaustively

00:22:30.990 --> 00:22:32.300
on their home page.

00:22:32.300 --> 00:22:35.670
And there was a leader board of
the most shared items from

00:22:35.670 --> 00:22:38.030
the Hangout app.

00:22:38.030 --> 00:22:42.120
So what they did with this data
is that Topshop used it

00:22:42.120 --> 00:22:44.390
to help its buyers decide what
they're going to actually

00:22:44.390 --> 00:22:45.680
bring to market.

00:22:45.680 --> 00:22:49.060
So what's really cool about this
is that Topshop fans get

00:22:49.060 --> 00:22:53.400
to influence the buying
decision.

00:22:53.400 --> 00:22:57.460
And what they saw was that
there was about 300,000

00:22:57.460 --> 00:23:00.480
followers to their page because
of this event in the

00:23:00.480 --> 00:23:02.160
two weeks leading up to it.

00:23:02.160 --> 00:23:07.180
And they had about 300% increase
in metrics like +1's

00:23:07.180 --> 00:23:10.010
and reshares and comments
per post.

00:23:10.010 --> 00:23:11.850
And they had really good
engagement in their Hangout

00:23:11.850 --> 00:23:13.940
app as well.

00:23:13.940 --> 00:23:18.360
So when we look to the future
of social experience online,

00:23:18.360 --> 00:23:21.760
it's our goal to give you the
tools to make any experience

00:23:21.760 --> 00:23:24.425
more social, personal
and meaningful.

00:23:27.450 --> 00:23:31.160
So a Page lets you talk
to your fans.

00:23:31.160 --> 00:23:34.020
And a Community lets
your users talk to

00:23:34.020 --> 00:23:36.181
each other about you.

00:23:36.181 --> 00:23:38.190
So Google+ Communities
are about

00:23:38.190 --> 00:23:41.860
connecting people and passions.

00:23:41.860 --> 00:23:44.810
They're a place for individuals,
organizations and

00:23:44.810 --> 00:23:48.585
businesses to meet and share
based on a common interest.

00:23:51.430 --> 00:23:54.120
And one way we've seen this work
is to build a community

00:23:54.120 --> 00:23:56.960
based on a topic that's
related to your brand.

00:23:56.960 --> 00:24:00.880
So in this case, this is
Lowe's Community Page.

00:24:00.880 --> 00:24:05.160
They built this Geek Your Home
community, where users can get

00:24:05.160 --> 00:24:09.250
together and share tips on
how to geek out your pad.

00:24:09.250 --> 00:24:11.120
And what's great is that
Lowe's is part of that

00:24:11.120 --> 00:24:12.370
conversation.

00:24:14.440 --> 00:24:18.940
And one of the other ways we've
seen Communities work is

00:24:18.940 --> 00:24:22.130
that you can listen to what
your customers are saying,

00:24:22.130 --> 00:24:25.950
both about your brand or topics
that are relevant to

00:24:25.950 --> 00:24:27.200
your business.

00:24:31.640 --> 00:24:37.260
So you should really create a
lasting impression by getting

00:24:37.260 --> 00:24:39.570
face to face with your
users in Hangouts.

00:24:39.570 --> 00:24:43.330
So that's sort of like one of
the ways we recommend you to

00:24:43.330 --> 00:24:46.120
grow your audience
with engagement.

00:24:46.120 --> 00:24:50.880
And then also create a more
social branded experience by

00:24:50.880 --> 00:24:53.810
creating a Hangout app.

00:24:53.810 --> 00:24:56.900
And then we recommend
participating in creating

00:24:56.900 --> 00:24:59.350
Communities as well, which
is another great way.

00:24:59.350 --> 00:25:02.720
And you can also listen to your
fans that way and hear

00:25:02.720 --> 00:25:03.970
what they have to say.

00:25:06.200 --> 00:25:10.880
So Google+ can also help you
achieve deeper engagement with

00:25:10.880 --> 00:25:15.450
your users, both on
your site and app.

00:25:15.450 --> 00:25:18.680
So this is where the Google+
platform comes in.

00:25:18.680 --> 00:25:20.950
And I'm not going to go too
deep into the platform,

00:25:20.950 --> 00:25:23.050
because there's been a lot
of sessions about it.

00:25:23.050 --> 00:25:26.800
I just want to briefly touch
on a couple of points here.

00:25:26.800 --> 00:25:28.980
One example that we launched
on Monday is content

00:25:28.980 --> 00:25:31.510
recommendations for your
mobile website.

00:25:31.510 --> 00:25:35.500
So when you help someone find a
great article on your site,

00:25:35.500 --> 00:25:38.190
you're not only making them
happier, you're inspiring

00:25:38.190 --> 00:25:40.930
deeper engagement and loyalty.

00:25:40.930 --> 00:25:44.190
So if you have a mobile website,
you should add this.

00:25:44.190 --> 00:25:48.730
And this is an example from
Forbes, where visitors to

00:25:48.730 --> 00:25:51.370
their mobile website can
now easily discover

00:25:51.370 --> 00:25:54.100
other content on Forbes.

00:25:54.100 --> 00:25:58.525
And this is an example, when you
integrate Google+ Sign In

00:25:58.525 --> 00:26:02.940
into your site, there's an
authentication dialog

00:26:02.940 --> 00:26:04.490
box that pops up.

00:26:04.490 --> 00:26:07.480
And one of the scopes that you
can have is with our YouTube

00:26:07.480 --> 00:26:13.460
API, so that when you sign in to
a site, you can also follow

00:26:13.460 --> 00:26:16.150
their YouTube channel
at the same time.

00:26:16.150 --> 00:26:19.890
So it's kind of connecting
your presence.

00:26:19.890 --> 00:26:24.160
They can follow your page later
on, but when you sign

00:26:24.160 --> 00:26:27.100
in, it's a great way to get more
followers to your YouTube

00:26:27.100 --> 00:26:28.350
channel as well.

00:26:30.710 --> 00:26:36.130
One of the most impressive
features of Google+ Sign In is

00:26:36.130 --> 00:26:38.500
something we call Over
The Air Installs.

00:26:38.500 --> 00:26:44.230
So when a user signs in on the
web, they can automatically

00:26:44.230 --> 00:26:47.550
choose to download your app to
their mobile phone without

00:26:47.550 --> 00:26:53.720
them ever leaving your site or
touching their device, which

00:26:53.720 --> 00:26:54.970
is pretty cool.

00:26:57.970 --> 00:27:01.130
And interactive posts allow
users to bring others they

00:27:01.130 --> 00:27:03.300
care about into your app.

00:27:03.300 --> 00:27:06.930
Users can send posts asking
people to sign up, write a

00:27:06.930 --> 00:27:10.120
review, register, buy something
or whatever

00:27:10.120 --> 00:27:12.010
your app calls for.

00:27:12.010 --> 00:27:19.100
In this example, Seth wants to
send a menu to Ardon and

00:27:19.100 --> 00:27:19.890
shared it on Google+.

00:27:19.890 --> 00:27:23.650
And then you see what the share
looks like for Ardon in

00:27:23.650 --> 00:27:24.850
the stream.

00:27:24.850 --> 00:27:27.620
And you see a View
Menu button?

00:27:27.620 --> 00:27:29.530
That's the really powerful
piece, is that there's a

00:27:29.530 --> 00:27:31.940
clickable call to action
embedded directly

00:27:31.940 --> 00:27:34.850
in a Google+ post.

00:27:34.850 --> 00:27:38.830
So this new call to action
allows you to not only share

00:27:38.830 --> 00:27:42.010
your content to a growing
audience but to also direct

00:27:42.010 --> 00:27:45.010
users what they should be
doing next in your app.

00:27:45.010 --> 00:27:46.930
Give them a reason to go
there and do something.

00:27:52.240 --> 00:27:55.680
So if it isn't already clear by
all of the Google+ Sign In

00:27:55.680 --> 00:27:59.280
talks at I/O, it's important.

00:27:59.280 --> 00:28:03.560
And it is the way to integrate
Google+ into your apps.

